Culture test:
These are test results for recovery cultures, pre-processing cultures etc, which can show presence of microorganisms or can be negative. There are 4 categories: C1, C2, C3 and C3A. Category 3 (C3) is unacceptable. For example: For Back Skin Recovery Culture 
 Category 1 
Result
Propionibacterium species.
Serology test: Final Laboratory test result report for a list of diseases including: HIV Ab I/II, HIV NAT, Hepatitis B and Hepatitis C tests of type Surface Antigen (HBsAg), Core Antibody (HBcAb) and NAT (HBV NAT, HCV NAT), Syphilis, HTLV I/II Antibody, CMV Antibody, WNV NAT, EBV or Toxoplasma, ABO-Rh etc. The results can be Non Reactive, Negative, Positive or Complete, with a Ref. range also mentioned.
